4.20	Masters_athletics	Masters athletics	Since at least the early 1930s, middle-aged athletes in Europe, Australia and New Zealand have competed with younger athletes, especially in cross country and road races. Some were active into their 50s. And on the track, Briton Don Finlay recorded a 14.4-second mark in the 120-yard high hurdles in 1949 at age 40, according to the biennial handbook published by World Masters Athletics.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/4/46/Paytonjordan.jpg
